egative lag, that holds for AGN spanning a large range of masses\n(about 2.5 orders of magnitude), thus supporting the idea that soft lags\noriginate in the innermost regions of AGN and are powerful tools for testing\ntheir physics and geometry.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Dec 2011 23:12:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 24 Feb 2013 21:38:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-03"}
